This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as person re-identification and attribute learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a semi-supervised attribute learning framework that involves training a deep Convolutional Neural Network (dCNN), which is a common technique used in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions using distance metrics and Cosine distance, which are commonly used in multimedia retrieval and matching, suggesting that it may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence, suggesting that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of techniques to improve the robustness of person re-identification, which may suggest that it belongs to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category, as robustness is an important aspect of security.
